impersonationleveldescription: other or logging error, see event for further details
this COM impersonation level hides the identity of the caller; calls to WMI may fail
this COM impersonation level allows objects to permit other objects to use credentials of the caller; may constitute unnecessary security risk; only supported under Windows 2000
this COM impersonation level allows objects to query the credentials of the caller; calls to WMI may fail
this COM impersonation level allows objects to use the credentials of the caller; RECOMMENDED impersonation level for WMI calls
